Hosting a Website with Azure Blob Storage

Start by searching for Storage Accounts in Azure and click Create.

Fill in the required details:
-Storage Account Name
-Region
-Performance: Standard
-Access Tier: Hot

After deployment, access the Storage Account from your resource group.

Under Containers, create a container (name it as desired) and upload your files.

Enable Static Website Hosting
- Open Visual Studio Code and install the Azure Storage extension.
- In the Storage Account, go to the Static Website section and enable it.
- Specify your Index and Error document names.
- Create a new folder in VSC and add index.html and error.html.
- Write the content for both HTML files and upload the folder by right-clicking.
- Select your subscription and deploy the files to Azure.
- After deployment, click on the notification to see your website live.
